  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "One of the most underrated romantic movies is **\"The Before Trilogy\"** by Richard Linklater, particularly the first installment, **\"Before Sunrise\" (1995)**. While it has a cult following, it often doesn't get the same mainstream attention as more conventional romantic films. The movie follows two strangers, Jesse (Ethan Hawke) and C\u00e9line (Julie Delpy), who meet on a train and spend one magical night wandering Vienna together, discussing life, love, and their dreams.  \n\nIts simplicity, heartfelt dialogue, and natural chemistry between the leads make it a deeply moving and authentic portrayal of love and connection. The sequels, **\"Before Sunset\" (2004)** and **\"Before Midnight\" (2013)**, continue their story in equally poignant ways, but the first film remains a hidden gem for those who haven't discovered it.  \n\nAnother underrated romantic movie is **\"In the Mood for Love\" (2000)** by Wong Kar-wai. This visually stunning film tells the story of two neighbors who suspect their spouses are having an affair and form a bond themselves. Its subtle, restrained romance and melancholic beauty make it a masterpiece that deserves more recognition.",
